Congressman Maurice Hinchey, a native New Yorker, has retired after serving the people of New York for over 35 years. Before entering politics, Hinchey served in the United States Navy. He then served as a member of the state assembly for 18 years, followed by 10 terms as a U.S. Representative for the 22nd Congressional District of New York. Throughout his career, Hinchey advocated for the middle class, renewable energy, Wall Street reform, and job creation. President Obama and the people of New York express their gratitude for his service.